Testing the API
You can test the API using curl or a tool like Postman:

Register a new user
bash
curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword123"
}' http://localhost:5000/register

Login
bash
curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "securepassword123"
}' http://localhost:5000/login

Access protected route (using the access token from login)
bash
curl -X GET -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN" http://localhost:5000/profile

Refresh token
bash
curl -X POST -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN" http://localhost:5000/refresh

Logout
bash
curl -X POST -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN" http://localhost:5000/logout
